four annual species of triglochin occur within the bioregion. they are distinguished from other wetland monocots by the combination of the following characters: leaf sheaths free, tiny leaf auricles present, , flowers in spikes or racemes, perianth present though small (<2 mm long),  and quickly deciduous, anthers sessile and each falling with a perianth segment, fruit finally separating into segments corresponding to the 3 fertile carpels, the carpels with basal spurs or appearing 6-pointed when viewed dorsally.
